Great ramen. I also regularly enjoy the curry rice. A great neighborhood spot!

Great ramen spot with attentive service. Ramen selections are solid and they can make it as spicy as you desire. Seaweed salad and gyoza are good. I've also enjoyed their ramen/gyoza mashup on the menu - very tasty!
You need to try this place! Ramen is great and taste so good, you could even make your own bowl! And the takoyaki absolutely taste good too! Will definitely come back. 10/10 would recommend.

One of my fav locations for tasty ramen. do yourself a favor and try this place. the staff was very welcoming and observant. i can see why they have a lot of positive reviews.

Great ramen! Also some of the best pork potstickers I’ve had. The reason it does not have five stars is because we did not enjoy the calamari. It’s basically just fried breading with a little calamari. It’s similar to an onion ring and lacks actual flavor. But great besides that. Will definitely be adding this place into my rotation.

Lakeview's Mile High Tanaka Ramen:  where Shinzo Abe would like to eat, and I'd like to invite him (and if he ever finds these messages, consider these words a real invitation to you, if he reads it and finds it).  The reason is I'm working on a children's book called Abe Lincoln: Land Surveyor from Illinois, and I'd love to hear his constructive criticism, and likely incorporate all of the feedback.  For Abe and Abe, despite the pronunciation variance, have the same high classic style of multilateral diplomacy: they know their foreign relations, or knew.  Shinzo, I haven't eaten here yet, but it's a real invitation, and then I could dedicate the book to him, although there's a lot of people that would share the list with him.  Lung Chu-Chen already did the leg work to get into my dedication page, but Shinzo Abe; well, I can't dedicate it to him with integrity.  I do like him though, and let's face it: not all Heads of State know their diplomacy, but Japan's does these days, right up there along with the German Chancellor.  I haven't eaten here yet, but I already know it's going to be good.  There's two vegan options here, although the first is labeled vegan.  I walked in there after having passed by with interest many times, and I remember: it really was for investigatory purposes: I'd probably be picking up some food there and not only was there one meal option: Tanaka Ramen in Lakeview has two.  The best part of course was that I think the girl I talked to was Japanese, and having been outside all day  rolling in the mud with my Shiba Inu, I wasn't expecting to pass by that ideal type of Japanese new friend, that you know everyone at work or school is competing to be friends with, we circled and passed, communicated under pandemic masks, which in my day of research at a few places, does add another barrier, but this Japanese beauty and I seemed to figure it all out in English in a few moments. There's two vegan options at Tanaka Ramen, for meals, clearly labeled, and a lot better than most places or nearly everywhere.  The second vegan option is label vegetarian which is actually true and accurate, for it's vegetarian and vegan.  And I think we were looking briefly at the ingredients, and confirmed: "There's two vegan options at this place: Tanaka Ramen."  All I can say is that one person left Tanaka Ramen thinking, "This place is the Athenian Candle Shop of Lakeview's restaurants: 100 Years more, I hope, and always called Tanaka Ramen for continuity.  I remember  clutching my Shiba Inu: a difficult breed in some ways, but also the best, and the right dog I knew I had to have a few years ago.  Who is the new "It" girl at the University of Chicago?  I was wondering what her subjects are, but it's better not to ask and just hope they are Linguistics, Romance Languages & Law.  I mean, she also may not necessarily have been a University of Chicago student, but she just seemed to do everything right.  Well, the person who stumbled in there today, the guy who desperately hopes to meet Shinzo Abe one day., where I'd probably just say nothing, but who knows: if he asked me questions about what I loved in Hiroshima, and the Japanese man who took me to the baseball stadium briefly and train station.  Literally, a person who saved my day, for I only had a day there, and the Japanese being the smartest, I  can't even remember how he helped me find the place, or who he was.  I must have asked someone for directions or looked lost. The person I'd really want to tell Shinzo Abe about is the Japanese girl on the blue trolly car.  For this many years after the trip, I'm wondering, "Did I add her on after?"  I'm pretty sure I didn't, and there was one girl in particular, who seemed to be checking me out, just as I was her. I'd tell Shinzo, "I think she understood the Nirvana shirt I wore, not only a Kurt Cobain tribute."  And the colorful cranes, of origami from the book about the girl with a name like Sadaku. I was visiting Chicago and we love Ramen so we decided to order Tanaka Ramen pick-up.  The good:  Ramen was tasty and overall the food tasted good.  The bad: We had ordered 3 Ramens and 2 appetizers (Tofu and Rock Shrimp).  When we were first given our order, it seemed like we were missing items.  Then, as we were leaving, the worker gave us the Tofu app.  Even so, seemed like there was food missing but I figured how can the mess this up, especially after initially forgetting the Tofu.  Well we get to the room and the Rock Shrimp was missing.  I was so upset but whatever, mistakes happen.  That is not the worst part.  When I call, the guy offers for me to walk back and pick it up.  No apology at all.  That is what got me steamed.  How hard is it to say " sorry for the mistake".  Nothing.  Nada.  Well, I told him I didn't want to walk back so please give me a refund for the app.  He said he would try and abruptly hung up.  Again, no " my bad" or anything.  How rude.  You would think that business being slow, they would appreciate the business.  I will never return to that restaurant.  Now am awaiting the refund.  Time will tell.  I recommend that if you do decide to visit, make sure to check your order.  If you want good customer service, go elsewhere.

Delicious

I celebrated my nomination earlier this evening in this delicious restaurant. I am glad to say that it was a astonishing evening and the place was evidently the reason for this fruitful gathering. The team  helped in a sweet manner, the food was very good and my guests were so  pleased. We shall absolutely visit again for more joyful events. thanks very much.

The atmosphere is phenomenal. When you walk in the vibe is very hip-earthy-posh with crazy sexy lighting. Dope music and authentic ramen and apps make for a nice bite, date, or pre night-out-on-the-town meal any night of the week. My recommendation... A spicy creamy vegan with a side of takoyaki.
Japanese Ramen restaurant

I arrive at this marvelous  restaurant every couple of days  as I like the good air that is part of this restaurant. The crew is very helpful and qualified. The service is absolutely efficient. Most important, the food they cook is first-rate. I came more than once and I was always joyful. The expense is decent. I highly suggest this place to all my friends.
This is my girlfriend's favorite ramen spot in the city, and she's totes a noodlehead. Make sure you get the seasoned egg.

I often take my friends to this restaurant with my highest recommendations. I visit this place often. This recommendation is always successful. The meals are flavorable and the team is attentive and cooperative. Every time  we go to this place we pass a gorgeous evening.  warmly recommended.
had a Tanaka spicy ramen topped with FRESH garlic. had median spicy, which was not really spicy, but the fresh garlic made up for that. it is the best ramen I'd had in Chicago.

A chic and fun place to get delicious ramen — and without breaking the bank! Pictures on the menu help visualize what you’re ordering. You’ll feel satiated and full but not bloated. The staff are welcoming and talkative. The only downside is that parking in the area is scarce, but for a casual date night, this is a great location!
The restaurant is nice and spacious, the food was delightful and the prices were very economical. fast, efficient service and very amiable staff. Highly recommended.

A random Google search for ramen led me here. Their Tanaka red spicy ramen was tasty. Mid level spice is enough to get the nose running, but the broth was still full of flavor. A very healthy portion of noodles and toppings made for a very filling meal.  This place is spacious and modern/hip. Will definitely be back to try other bowls.

Had their chicken wonton ramen. It was really delicious and filled you up.  Get it with a soft boiled egg.   I also tried their gyoza and salad. Both were tasty and the salad was very refreshing.  Also try their hot sauce which is made in house. It has the perfect amount of spice and a really nice kick to it. Perfect to add to the ramen!

Ramen was quite good, but would probably only order takeout in the future. Restaurant was quite cold, and seats were horribly uncomfortable. We couldn’t even take our winter coats off. Minimal drink options, not even hot tea, just cans of soda and water.

It was amazing! If Ichiraku Ramen was real, this would be it! Naruto would be proud! The delicious broth and chewy noodles made my night! Thanks Tanaka! I will be visiting more often
So delicious!
I had the vegan Tanaka bowl. So flavorful! The staff was very friendly and prompt with our orders. Definitely will recommend and revisit!

I've been lookin for a place that makes Ramen as good as in Japan. I lived there for two years and now I'm having a hard time finding a decent ramen that is just as good but this places comes so close! The broth has so much flavor! And the ramen noodles are so authentic is was such a great bowl of ramen. I also ordered gyozas and they were delicious and just as good as Japan as well. I also got a delicious pork bun and an order of the fried chicken appetizer. The fried chicken was seasoned with too much pepper and when I bit into it l, it was kind of touch to bite into because the way the chicken was cut.  The server was nice however she only refilled my water once and a second time when I asked. I am always drinking water so I was out pretty quickly. There was also a couple that kept staring at me and making me feel super uncomfortable. I was eating alone though so I'm guessing they thought it was a strange thing. Never the less the atmosphere was great and they were not busy at all. It was Saturday around 3pm when I came in.

We kept ignoring this restaurant as it was just down the road. We finally took the plunge and it was absolutely fab! Loved the food - we had a mix of different dishes from Ramen to appetizers. Well priced, quick and friendly service. Will definitely go there again!
Really flavorful ramen (my favourite is the tanake chicken red) served quickly. I also liked the karaage chicken and the matcha mochi!
The menu pictures looks like they're served on plates, but it comes in a bowl and it's like a soup.
Really good ramen place with nice decor, huge bowls, and kind servers! Their fried brussel sprout bowl is really good.

Slightly pricey but definitely worth it. The eel don and ramen are very solicitous. If ordered as to go or pick up, Tanaka Ramen would pack the soup and noodles separately so it would never be soggy. Takoyaki are yummy too.
I love this spot. Some of the best ramen in Lincoln Park.  Staff is friendly atmosphere and decor is cute. Definitely stop by if you are in the area.

Tucked away on Diversey, it can be hard to spot from the streets but a nice little ramen shop, especially for the cold Chicago winter months. Staff was Friendly and service was quick, I had the takoyaki and the spicy black ramen, a pork broth with a generous portion of meat and noodles. Great for groups and no need for reservations​.
Great ramen and great service. Came in for a birthday and they kept bringing out Saki bombs
I feel like this place has decreased in quality over time.
Very GOOD

The only FISH + CHICKEN Ramen Broth in Chicago.  Unfortunately, thick noodles texture feels like stir-fry Chinese noodles. Chashu had porky smell.  Combination is NOT a deal as it has lesser and substituted items. Skip the all green SALAD with a slab of gingery dressing.  4-pc CRISPY CHICKEN instead of the usual 6-pcs from regular menu for $6.  Maybe, food will be better in the future. It's a good menu.
Nice staff, great environment. The ramen broth, egg, and pork were great. The noodles were undercooked (mushy and white on the inside).  Sent the first bowl back and second came back the same.
One of top ramen spots in chicago

I was so surprised how empty the place was because the setting and staff are so nice! The waitress saw my hair tie broke and before I could even process it she handed me hers! Not to mention the food was delicious! The chicken karage was to die for and my ramen bowl was full to the top with all sorts of extras. If you come here on a date, impress your girl by ordering the bottle of strawberry nigori! I'm from New York City and to get ramen like this you would have to wait for an hour in Manhattan. This place deserves more customers and you should treat yourself to some ramen.
I love the Tanaka Red Spicy. Appetizers are meh, the Gyoza could use a little more flavor.

My review is for the ramen they are selling through Fooda. I had the classic Tonkatsu ramen and while the broth was great and toppings were good, the noodles were horrible. Apparently the noodles they serve and deliver as part of their daily business are much better/bigger, but these were the thinnest, mushiest noodles I have ever eaten in anything let alone ramen.  I appreciate a lot of the efforts being made to make ramen in this form deliverable during the lunch hour to large business locations, but at over $8 for a pile of mushy noodles and two pieces of pork I was a dissapointed. Again, the broth was fantastic and I am sure they do a much better job in their actual restaurant, but if you cant fix the noodles, you shouldn't call what you serve through Fooda ramen.

Great food and awesome decor however they keep messing up my deliveries orders and today, I am pretty sure they replace what was suppose to be chasu pork with just chicken. One time, I ordered 2 orders of tajoyaki. They only sent me 1 order and didn't deliver another one or reimburse me. Just pay attention to what you do.

Really enjoyed the Tanaka Red ramen and I had some left over to take home. You can pick the spice level and the vegetables and meat were fresh. Both service and food prep time was fast.
This place is great! I really hope they stick around. Best vegan ramen in Chicago.
I had the Tanaka Red. It was so good! Friendly staff and super quick carry out!

I wasn't sure about their (jinya) new changes, but oh my god I'm so glad we came back. We used to love it before and it's as if they even improved! Their classic and chicken red ramen were perfect and I can't wait to come back!
